HEADWORD: Muzzle-loader
<hw>Muz"zle-load`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A firearm
which receives its charge through the muzzle, as distinguished from one
which is loaded at the breech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

